[h1]Phobos' Industrial Pathways: Biomass — Changelog[/h1]

[h2]v1.4.0 — Medicinal Effects & Moodle Framework (2026-03-08)[/h2]

[h3]New Features[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Medicated custom moodle[/b] — Medicinal hemp items (poultice, tincture) trigger a Medicated moodle via Moodle Framework integration. Configurable duration. Graceful no-op when Moodle Framework is not installed.
[*] [b]Medicinal timed actions[/b] — Poultice and tincture now have timed application actions with visual and audio feedback instead of instant use.
[*] [b]Hemp product effects system[/b] — Doubled base effects on hemp products. New effects on decarboxylated buds and sugar syrup.
[*] [b]33 new sandbox options[/b] — New PCP_HempEffects settings page with per-product stat tuning for pipes, cigars, cigarettes, decarbed buds, poultice, tincture, sugar syrup, plus moodle duration controls.
[*] [b]EnableDebugLogging sandbox option[/b] — Centralised debug logging via PhobosLib_Debug.
[*] [b]Fermentation tooltip[/b] — Canned hemp buds show dynamic curing progress (%) and estimated days remaining. Canning date stamped on creation and displayed in tooltip.
[*] [b]Improved static tooltips[/b] — Explicit ~4 week curing duration and "not spoilage" clarification on fermentable items.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Cigar recipe[/b] — Now uses tobacco leaves + sugar with partial sugar consumption (was incorrectly consuming full sugar item).
[*] [b]Horticulture migration re-runnable[/b] — Migration sandbox flag can now be re-enabled for repeated use.
[*] [b]Drainable migration RuntimeException[/b] — Fixed crash in drainable item migration path.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] Sandbox options: 19 to [b]52[/b] (+33 on PCP_HempEffects page)
[*] Requires [b]PhobosLib 1.18.0+[/b] (was 1.16.0+)
[*] Optional: [b]Moodle Framework[/b] (new soft dependency)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.3.0 — Hemp Expansion & Audit (2026-03-08)[/h2]
[list]
[*] Added 6 new items: Seed Press Cake, Hemp Sack, Oakum, Hemp Fishing Net, Hemp Sheet Rope, Hemp Snare
[*] Vanilla station integration: Scutching Board, Simple Loom, Full Loom, Hand Press
[*] Mechanical hazard system: smoke inhalation and mineral dust with light PPE tier (dust mask sufficient)
[*] Oakum as alternative reinforcement in hempcrete recipes
[*] Seed Press Cake as universal oil pressing byproduct (all 12 mortar/lab recipes)
[*] HempScutched acceptance expanded across all fiber-consuming recipes
[*] Diversified skill requirements: Farming, Tailoring, Fishing, Trapping
[*] 26 new ZScienceSkill specimen registrations (horticulture, salt, hemp expansion)
[*] Expanded world loot distributions to 13 additional B42 locations
[*] Gas Mask Filter recipe now cross-trains Doctor skill
[*] Art style guidelines documented for contributors
[*] 15 non-conforming icons identified for regeneration
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.2.0 — Botanical & Horticulture Pathway (2026-03-06)[/h2]

[h3]New Features[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Botanical Pathway[/b] — 30 new recipes for hemp processing across 4 crafting tiers:
  — [b]Retting & Extraction[/b] (7): Chemical retting with KOH/NaOH, fiber/hurd splitting, seed threshing
  — [b]Textiles[/b] (5): Spin twine, braid rope, weave cloth, layer canvas, tar rope
  — [b]Papermaking[/b] (5): Boil pulp, NaOH chemical pulping, press paper sheets
  — [b]Medicinal[/b] (4): Herb poultice, alcohol tincture
  — [b]Hurd Processing[/b] (5): Char to charcoal, compost, fire bundles
  — [b]Cross-Pathway[/b] (3+1): Hemp bandages, hempcrete (mixer), tarred rope
[*] [b]13 botanical items[/b] — RettedHempStalk, HempBastFiber, HempHurd, HempTwine, HempRope, TarredHempRope, HempCloth, HempCanvas, HempPulp, HempPaper, HempPoultice, HempTincture, HempcreteBlock
[*] [b]31 horticulture items[/b] — Full parity with [B42] Horticulture mod: tobacco (4), hemp buds (9), papermaking (5), smoking (10), cooking (3)
[*] [b]Horticulture migration system[/b] — Dual-trigger: manual sandbox button (works while Horticulture still subscribed) + automatic orphan detection after unsubscription. Preserves fill level, condition, and wet state.
[*] [b]MigrateHorticultureItems sandbox option[/b] — One-shot migration on PCP_Reset page
[*] [b]EnableBotanicalPathway sandbox option[/b] — Master switch for botanical recipes (default: ON)
[*] [b]SkillPurityInfluence sandbox option[/b] — Applied Chemistry skill effect on purity (None/Low/Standard/High)
[*] [b]19 OpenAI-generated icons[/b] — 6 regenerated chemistry icons + 13 new botanical pathway icons
[*] [b]6 category recipe books[/b] — Field Chemistry Primer, Kitchen Chemistry Companion, Laboratory Chemistry Reference, Industrial Processes Manual, Botanical Horticulture Guide, plus Complete Chemistry Compendium (master volume teaching all recipes)
[*] [b]PCPMixReinforcedHempcrete (H14b)[/b] — Tarred rope reinforcement for hempcrete blocks via concrete mixer
[*] [b]base:rope tags[/b] — HempRope and TarredHempRope tagged with base:rope for vanilla recipe substitution
[*] [b]TarredHempRope as campfire fuel[/b] — FireFuelRatio 0.5 for use as fire-starting material
[*] [b]Phobos Horticulture crafting category[/b] — Dedicated crafting tab for horticulture recipes
[*] [b]41 missing recipe translations fixed[/b] — Added EN translation entries for all untranslated recipe names
[*] [b]Crafting categories renamed[/b] — Category display names updated to use spaces for clean UI presentation
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]CTD: Invalid item references in botanical recipes[/b] — Fixed Base.SodiumHydroxide, Base.AlcoholBandages, Base.WhiskeyFull/Half references
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]EnableImpuritySystem default = TRUE[/b] (was false); one-time migration popup for existing worlds
[*] Recipe count: 234 to [b]276[/b] (42 new recipes)
[*] Item count: 91 to [b]101[/b] (6 recipe books + 4 new items)
[*] Tradeable items: 34 to [b]59[/b]
[*] ZScience specimens: 33 to [b]52[/b] items + 8 fluids
[*] OnCreate callbacks: 168 to [b]216[/b]
[*] Crafting categories: 4+mixer to [b]5+mixer[/b] (added Phobos Horticulture)
[*] Sandbox options: 17 to [b]19[/b]
[*] Requires [b]PhobosLib 1.16.0+[/b]
[*] [b]Mod renamed[/b] — Display name changed from "Phobos' Chemistry Pathways" to "Phobos' Industrial Pathways: Biomass" as part of the new Phobos' Industrial Pathways mod series. Internal mod ID and all save data remain unchanged.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.1.0 — Skill Purity Influence (2026-03-06)[/h2]

[h3]New Features[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]SkillPurityInfluence sandbox option[/b] — Controls Applied Chemistry skill effect on output purity (None/Low/Standard/High, default: Standard)
[*] [b]Impurity default migration[/b] — One-time notice popup auto-enables impurity system for existing worlds
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
